===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} [[Ἀγαμέμνων]] (Agamemnon) "very resolute"

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# {{cattag|Greek mythology}} One of the most distinguished [[hero]]es of [[Greek]] [[mythology]]. He is the son of King [[Atreus]] of [[Mycenae]] and Queen Aerope, and brother of [[Menelaus]]. He is attributed with [[rally]]ing the [[Greek]]s for the [[w:Trojan War|Trojan War]]

